<div id="banner">
	<h1>Lessons in Capitalism #1: Division of Labor</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>When I was in first grade, I imagined that there was another me, up in heaven, and we&#8217;d take shifts using my body. I wouldn&#8217;t know who had done what because he&#8217;d leave all his memories in the body. So whenever things got really bad, I&#8217;d ask him to take his shift. I even recall switching with him, although I&#8217;m not sure how&#8230; I must have thought I wasn&#8217;t really conscious.</p>

<p class="posted">posted March 26, 2005 04:05 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_education">Education</a>) (<a href="001632#comments">0 comments</a>) <a href="001632" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

